Through one unified platform, it integrates telemedicine, pharmacy e-commerce, preventive health content, and AI-driven analytics — ensuring a seamless and trusted healthcare journey. Patients can access certified doctors, book visits, perform televisits, receive medications at home, and follow personalized health programs. Healthcare providers gain intuitive digital tools to manage bookings, consultations, e-commerce, and patient communication from a single interface. Built with full EU and HIPAA compliance, Salute360 empowers hospitals, pharmacies, insurers, and employers to deliver smarter, more connected, and patient-centered care. Already trusted by 200,000 patients and 8,000 healthcare professionals, Salute360 bridges fragmented healthcare services into one coherent ecosystem, enabling scalable growth and measurable impact on global well-being.

description:

Possibia is the agentic AI platform that fixes this. We connect patients, hospitals, sponsors, and advocacy groups in one intelligent network, making trials discoverable, workflows seamless, and engagement both fast and transparent. Possibia is the infrastructure the trial ecosystem has been missing — efficient, ethical, intelligent. 

As the Winner of Norway’s 100 Pitches 2025, we’re reshaping how research moves from idea to life-saving impact.

Hope is easier to find when you know where to look — and it starts with Possibia.

As the energy transition accelerates and skilled labor shortages deepen, Chapter’s specialized AI infrastructure becomes increasingly mission-critical, forming a defensible position at the intersection of knowledge automation and the clean energy economy.

name: arterioscope FlexCo
shortDescription: arterioscope is a medtech AI spin-off from Graz University of Technology developing digital biomarker diagnostics. Our patented technology non-invasively derives cardiac biomarkers — starting with NT-
description: arterioscope is a medtech AI spin-off from Graz University of Technology developing digital biomarker diagnostics. Our patented technology non-invasively derives cardiac biomarkers — starting with NT-proBNP — directly from ECG and PPG signals processed by advanced machine learning models. NT-proBNP is the gold standard for heart failure diagnostics, but today requires costly and invasive blood tests. By leveraging data from a simple ECG or PPG, we enable earlier detection of heart failure, faster triage in primary care, and significant cost savings for healthcare providers and pharma. Beyond NT-proBNP, our platform is designed to expand to additional biomarkers — including renal function (eGFR) — creating the first scalable AI platform for digital biomarker diagnostics. We have proven our technology in clinical studies, secured pilot customers, and are now raising our seed round to bring the first AI-ECG biomarker product to market.

shortDescription: Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.
description:
Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.
In essence, we’re building a P2P risk-sharing network where a group of individuals with mutual interests or similar risk profiles pool their “premiums” together to insure against a risk. Our platform enables individuals with similar interests to share the risk between themselves, whether based on shared interests, community ties, or specific needs. Often these individuals are somehow connected, e.g. personally (friends), or through mutual business or other common criteria (e.g. possession or similar interests). These groups are then free to define their terms, set coverage limits, and even manage claims. That significantly diverges from traditional insurance
models by community-centric insurance ecosystem, utilizing decentralization and advanced technologies.

description: PhotonSense Tech is a German startup specializing in innovative photonic sensor solutions designed to enhance safety, sustainability, and operational efficiency. The company focuses on real-time air quality monitoring and structural integrity analysis for industries such as building construction, bridge maintenance, and rail infrastructure. Their products detect multiple gases, chemical warfare agents, and early signs of corrosion with highly sensitive laser-based sensors capable of identifying pollutants at thresholds below one part per billion (ppb). PhotonSense Tech integrates advanced technologies, including laser backscattering, optoelectronics, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and the Internet of Things (IoT), to deliver precise, actionable environmental insights. Additionally, their systems leverage Big Data platforms to analyze trends, optimize decision-making, and enhance predictive analytics. By combining AI with cloud-based analytics, the company offers solutions that enable real-time threat detection, pattern recognition, and automated calibration for improved accuracy and reduced false positives. The startup's value proposition lies in its ability to redefine environmental monitoring and predictive analysis with unmatched precision, reliability, and speed, empowering industries to proactively address safety concerns while contributing to cleaner environments and safer communities. Notable differentiators include their advanced detection capabilities, integration of multiple cutting-edge technologies, and a commitment to quality and innovation. PhotonSense Tech positions itself as a leader in the photonic sensing market, offering transformative solutions for businesses seeking to excel in a data-driven, sustainable future.

Such s
description:
We are developing a platform that allows anyone to easily fine-tune small language model (SLMs). 
How easily? Imagine writing an in-context learning prompt to an LLM with a few dozen examples.

Such specialized SLMs can solve specific tasks at much lower latency and cost than generic, pre-trained LLMs while maintaining accuracy. Additionally their small size allow for local deployment – leveraging the benefits of CPU inference (speed, cost, security, networking, reduced dependencies).

Our hypothesis is that such small models will be the building blocks of highly performant multi-agentic AI products of the future.

name: Flexora
shortDescription: Flexora provides customizable, non-invasive flexible sensor technology that enables real-time monitoring, predictive maintenance, and process optimization through wireless data acquisition for improved operational efficiency and sustainability.
description: Flexora is a technology-driven startup specializing in advanced sensor solutions designed for large-scale data acquisition and process improvement. Their core product is an intelligent adhesive sensor film based on flexible foil, which can monitor various physical parameters like temperature over extensive surfaces. This film offers retrofit installation and wireless data transfer capabilities, making it an efficient and non-invasive solution for enterprises seeking to optimize their operations. Flexora's technology supports applications such as predictive maintenance, operational safety enhancement, hydraulic system optimization, and anomaly detection, enabling companies to reduce unplanned downtime, energy consumption, and CO₂ emissions, while increasing productivity and profitability. The sensors are printed on customizable substrates, allowing tailored solutions for specific customer requirements. Targeting industries with complex machinery, infrastructure, and systems, Flexora empowers businesses to make data-driven decisions and achieve sustainable improvements in processes and performance. Originating from the Dresden Integrated Center for Applied Physics and Photonic Materials, the company leverages cutting-edge research and a collaborative network to deliver impactful innovations. Funded by the German Federal Ministry for Economics and Energy and the European Social Fund (via the EXIST program), Flexora is committed to driving progress, unlocking efficiencies, and enabling new business models through its versatile sensor technology.

name: Danvantar Biophotonics
shortDescription: Danvantar Biophotonics develops innovative photobiomodulation devices that combine therapy and monitoring to accelerate chronic wound healing, offering affordable, home-based solutions to improve patient outcomes and reduce healthcare costs.
description: Danvantar Biophotonics is a startup focused on revolutionizing chronic wound care using precision photonics technology. The company has developed an advanced photobiomodulation (PBM) device that combines therapeutic treatment and monitoring capabilities to accelerate the healing process for chronic wounds such as diabetic foot ulcers. These conditions affect millions globally, often leading to severe complications like pain, amputations, and rising healthcare expenses. Danvantar's innovative approach targets the inefficiencies in current treatment methods, which are often costly, slow, and reliant on frequent clinical interventions. Their device is designed to be smart, scalable, and affordable, with a strong emphasis on enabling home-based and self-care solutions. By shifting treatment to the comfort of patients' homes, the company addresses the largest cost driver in chronic wound management, while also providing a quick, safe, and user-friendly solution. Danvantar Biophotonics leverages precision photonics technology to enhance the healing process, setting itself apart with its unique combination of therapy and monitoring features. Their solution not only aims to improve patient outcomes but also offers significant cost savings for healthcare systems. This disruptive approach positions the company as a key player in addressing the chronic wound crisis with cutting-edge, patient-centric technology.

name: Hyphorest
shortDescription: Hyphorest provides satellite-monitored, AI-driven nature restoration projects with transparent, verifiable data for compliance reporting and environmental contributions.
description: Hyphorest is a startup focused on connecting individuals and organizations to verified nature restoration projects, leveraging advanced satellite monitoring and AI technology. Their platform tracks CO₂ sequestration, biodiversity indicators, and ecosystem health to deliver transparent, third-party verified data. The company caters primarily to businesses seeking compliance-ready reporting for sustainability standards such as CSRD (Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive) and TNFD (Taskforce on Nature-related Financial Disclosures), as well as individuals looking to make credible environmental contributions. Key offerings include selecting vetted restoration projects—such as reforestation, wetlands, mangroves, and regenerative agriculture—tracking impact through satellite data, and downloading annual compliance reports formatted for auditors and stakeholders. Hyphorest differentiates itself by eliminating greenwashing risks via continuous monitoring and providing data that goes beyond carbon metrics, supporting full nature-related disclosures. Their easy-to-use dashboard is tailored for corporate sustainability managers, simplifying adoption for teams without technical expertise in forestry or environmental sciences. The company also offers an October 2025 pilot program, allowing early participants to fund restoration projects and receive satellite-verified impact reports while positioning themselves as nature-positive leaders. Supported by ESA-BIC funding and led by experts in AI, machine learning, blockchain, and enterprise software, Hyphorest aims to revolutionize environmental impact tracking and reporting by making it transparent, actionable, and accessible to all stakeholders.

name: Elixion Medical
shortDescription: Automated medical monitoring for hospitals.
description: Developer of health-tech company intended to ease care shortage in hospitals and nursing homes with medical IoT and SaaS. The company offers automated catheter and drain monitoring with a medical IoT, SaaS and AI platform, which delivers real-time data and uses machine learning to forecast the healing process for earlier drain and catheter removal and also enables early detection of complications and infections to improve patient safety.

name: Tiplo
shortDescription: Tiplo is transforming musculoskeletal (MSK) rehabilitation through intelligent, sensor-integrated software that enables patients to recover effectively from home. By connecting with our single IMU (In
description: Tiplo is transforming musculoskeletal (MSK) rehabilitation through intelligent, sensor-integrated software that enables patients to recover effectively from home. By connecting with our single IMU (Inertial Monitoring Unit) motion sensor, Tiplo’s platform captures accurate movement data, delivering real-time feedback to patients and actionable insights to clinicians. The system reduces clinic capacity strain, improves adherence, and scales capacity across physiotherapy networks. For insurers and corporates, Tiplo provides measurable recovery data, faster return-to-work outcomes, and reduced long-term healthcare costs. Designed for simplicity, accessibility, and clinical scalability and credibility, Tiplo bridges the gap between in-person and remote physiotherapy—empowering clinicians, patients, and partners with smarter, data-driven rehabilitation.

name: CyberSmart
shortDescription: Comprehensive cybersecurity solutions for SMEs.
description: Provider of an all-in-one cybersecurity platform that offers monitoring, optimization, training, and insurance solutions. The platform delivers continuous compliance and protection against cyber threats. It primarily serves small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) seeking comprehensive cybersecurity measures.

name: Compliance Consulting Operations GmbH
shortDescription: Compliance Consulting Operations GmbH provides regulatory compliance solutions through their COR3 platform, simplifying legal processes and ensuring efficient, secure, and cost-effective adherence to regulations for businesses in regulated industries.
description: Compliance Consulting Operations GmbH specializes in providing end-to-end regulatory compliance solutions tailored for businesses in regulated industries such as banking, finance, insurance, and legal services. Their flagship product, COR3, is a comprehensive compliance management platform designed to simplify legal processes, reduce operational burden, and ensure adherence to regulations like DORA, GDPR, and ISO27001 standards. COR3 offers two tiers: COR3 End-To-End, which includes advanced features such as workflow automation, risk analysis, dashboards, and implementation tracking; and COR3 ZEN, a streamlined option focused on providing essential legal inventory and regulatory screening without additional workflows. Both tiers leverage cutting-edge technology, including AI-driven analysis and hybrid solutions for translating complex legal language into actionable insights. The platform focuses on noise-canceling by filtering out irrelevant norms, providing only binding regulations, and enabling structured, audit-proof documentation. Targeting compliance departments, risk management teams, boards, and advisors, the company's solutions address pain points like resource inefficiency and regulatory complexity. With 15 years of expertise and a proven track record in MaRisk compliance, the company boasts 93% accuracy in norm delivery and promises up to 75% reduction in compliance-related workload. Their systems are hosted on secure servers in Germany, ensuring data privacy and regulatory integrity. Compliance Consulting Operations GmbH differentiates itself with its clarity, efficiency, and security in legal handling, empowering organizations to focus on strategic decisions while minimizing risks associated with legal obligations.

name: Surg storage Co., Ltd.
shortDescription: Surg storage is a Japan-based healthtech startup providing a medical data platform that accelerates AI innovation in healthcare. We specialize in structuring and standardizing complex data such as sur
description:
Surg storage is a Japan-based healthtech startup providing a medical data platform that accelerates AI innovation in healthcare. We specialize in structuring and standardizing complex data such as surgical videos, diagnostic imaging, and EHRs, enabling developers and institutions to access reliable, interoperable datasets.

With collaborations across 137 hospitals, we have built one of the world’s largest ethically approved and annotated surgical video repositories, exceeding 7,000 cases. Our services include secure data licensing, expert annotation, joint R&D, and regulatory support for PMDA, FDA, and CE submissions.

Focusing on oncology, neurology, and cardiovascular medicine, we deliver a trusted foundation for safe, fair, and transparent medical AI. Our goal is to become the global hub for structured medical data, reducing clinician burden while improving healthcare quality worldwide.

Our tech stack provide LLM, speech, vision and satellite pipelines with optimization, forecasting, causality and anomaly detection. Building on this engine, LumCall reinvents contact centres, Wircle unifies HR and projects, Strage powers data-led campaigns, Tenance becomes the knowledge aide, Triact delivers digital triage, and Jurne automates newsrooms. Complementary solutions—from subscriber segmentation and pricing simulation to EV-charge analytics, rheumatology diagnosis and tampered-image detection—show how we FOCUS BEYOND, turning raw data into trusted decisions for government, banking, retail, energy, media and healthcare clients alike.

name: Vindi Biosystems
shortDescription: Vindi Biosystems is developing PICTURE™, a next-generation wearable platform that uses photonic-integrated-circuit (PIC) sensors to continuously track biochemical biomarkers in real time. Our technolo
description:
Vindi Biosystems is developing PICTURE™, a next-generation wearable platform that uses photonic-integrated-circuit (PIC) sensors to continuously track biochemical biomarkers in real time. Our technology is built around a patent-pending MMI-based refractive-index sensor with single-wavelength optical readout, enabling laboratory-grade detection in a compact, low-power, and affordable form factor.

We combine advanced integrated photonics, low-noise analog electronics, and machine-learning algorithms to deliver actionable physiological insights for research use and future health-monitoring applications. Our system is designed for continuous, non-invasive biochemical tracking, offering a new layer of data beyond traditional heart rate or motion sensors.

Vindi aims to enable next-generation digital health, hormonal monitoring, and personalized wellness through high-resolution biochemical sensing-anytime, anywhere.

name: Icarus
shortDescription: Icarus leverages artificial intelligence to enhance patient care for chronic and post-operative conditions, offering clinics and healthcare institutions AI-driven models for continuous, automated follow-up and monitoring.
description: Icarus is a start-up that uses artificial intelligence to improve the care of patients with chronic or post-operative conditions. Icarus provides clinics and healthcare institutions with an artificial intelligence model that can replace physicians in post-operative and post-diagnosis follow-up for round-the-clock patient care.

name: Cognovo Oy
shortDescription: Cognovo Oy provides AI-powered integration, automation, and strategic solutions to streamline operations, reduce costs, and enable scalable growth for enterprises and SMEs using human-centered technologies and best practices.
description: Cognovo Oy is a Finland-based startup founded in 2025 that focuses on providing AI-powered integration and automation solutions to enterprises and SMEs. The company addresses challenges such as operational inefficiencies, resource scarcity, and system complexities by offering four primary services: system integration, process automation, AI-driven solutions, and advisory/strategy development. Their system integration services unify ERP, CRM, HR, finance, and custom applications into a secure and scalable ecosystem, eliminating the need for cumbersome point-to-point integrations. Process automation solutions minimize manual tasks and errors, improving data accuracy and operational efficiency. Cognovo also offers AI-powered workflows that enhance employee experiences, assist decision-making, and optimize productivity while maintaining data security. Additionally, their advisory and strategy services ensure that automation initiatives follow best practices and align with long-term business objectives. Cognovo's target market includes enterprises and SMEs looking to modernize their operations, reduce costs, and scale effectively in an increasingly complex digital landscape. Their approach emphasizes reliability, scalability, and alignment with strategic goals, leveraging deep expertise in leading platforms and human-centered AI technologies. Differentiators include their focus on vendor-recommended best practices and their vision of creating seamless, connected systems powered by intelligent automation. With a mission to simplify complexity and a future-ready outlook, Cognovo Oy positions itself as a key partner for businesses aiming to operate more efficiently and intelligently in the age of AI.

name: AIHI (AI for Humanitarian Impact)
shortDescription: AIHI establishes governance frameworks and delivers tailored programs to enable safe, ethical, and effective AI deployment in humanitarian actions and crisis response.
description: AIHI (AI for Humanitarian Impact) focuses on equipping humanitarian organizations with robust AI governance frameworks to ensure the safe, ethical, and productive deployment of artificial intelligence in crisis response and humanitarian actions. The startup offers specialized programs designed for various organizational roles, including executives, compliance teams, fundraising professionals, and operational teams. Their services include AI readiness assessments, strategic training, policy development, compliance guidance, and hands-on pilot implementations. AIHI's mission is to establish standards that safeguard the use of AI while amplifying its potential to improve fundraising success, logistical speed, cybersecurity measures, precision targeting of vulnerable populations, and workforce efficiency. Notable programs include 'AI for Humanitarian Leaders' for executives, 'AI Ethics & Compliance' for legal teams, and 'AI for Revenue Generation' for fundraising teams. These programs feature tailored deliverables, such as governance packs, risk scenarios, audit reports, and compliance templates. AIHI employs a strategic consulting approach, working closely with clients to develop implementation roadmaps and operational frameworks over defined timeframes ranging from 4 to 12 months. Their services are trusted by prominent humanitarian organizations, including Save the Children, UNHCR, Oxfam, and OCHA. AIHI's core value proposition lies in its commitment to helping organizations leverage AI as a transformative tool while mitigating risks and ensuring ethical standards are upheld. Partnering with Valtium & Company for delivery, AIHI positions itself as a critical enabler of AI readiness and governance in the humanitarian sector.

name: MicroAGI
shortDescription: AI platform for industrial optimization.
description: Developer of an artificial intelligence platform designed to optimize asset performance and enhance cybersecurity in industrial settings. The platform features real-time machine sensor data analysis, AI and ML model deployment on smart devices, predictive maintenance, network optimization, and agentless machine learning for IT and OT ecosystems.

name: Flow Technologies
shortDescription: Flow Technologies is a B2B SaaS digital health company transforming how clinics and hospitals deliver care. Our platform, Flowzone, replaces fragmented tools with one integrated solution that enables
description: Flow Technologies is a B2B SaaS digital health company transforming how clinics and hospitals deliver care. Our platform, Flowzone, replaces fragmented tools with one integrated solution that enables therapists and healthcare providers to follow up patients before, during, and after treatment. By unifying workflows and structuring health data, Flowzone makes daily work more efficient for providers, improves treatment outcomes for patients, and creates the foundation for AI-driven insights and innovation. We focus on rehabilitation, hospitals, and mental health, where the need for continuous follow-up and data-driven care is greatest. Flowzone is already the market leader in Norway’s private rehab sector and is scaling into Germany with major clinic groups.
